A film by @type7

Son of legendary Australian shaper and surfer Neal Purchase, Neal Purchase Jnr was more or less born into the profession and culture. Growing up competing, Neal found his way as a free surfer, later following his father’s footsteps as a shaper. Now, Neal is renowned internationally for his surfing ability as well as his craftsmanship.

His iconic Duo, Quartet and Single fin shapes are a modern day homage to the past, something he credits to his father’s influence. An ever evolving refinement of classic designs, Neal’s boards are just as much a work of art as they are high performance surf craft. 

Yet despite his status in the surf world, 'Purcho' is one of the most kind, humble people you will meet. In fact, he scored the soundtrack for this very film 🏄‍♂️

Directed by @caplice
Starring @nealpurchasejnr

The Canadian town of Whistler might be better known for its winter skiing but this house, perched on a cliffside at the famous resort, might be making a case for it being a killer summer destination. Designed by @gortscott this home sits overlooking one of the many tranquil lakes in the area.

It completely avoids any standard tropes of mountain living, foregoing wood for sharp, minimal concrete interiors which leave the dramatic landscapes visible outside to be the centre of attention ⛰️

Photos by @arorygardiner

node.text:
This hilltop home in New South Wales might look almost impenetrable at first, but step inside and you are greeted by a view over the lush landscape and a collection of wood and warm-hued furniture. 

Designed by architect studio @editionoffice, the dark exterior is created using a combination of pigmented concrete and blackened timber, which the studio describe as giving a shadow-like effect on the landscape from a distance. Inside, dark corridors give way to bright wood floors, expansive views over the surrounding forests, and a shallow pool on the lower floor, which not only provides a small quiet space but also works to passively cool the house by cooling the air flow coming into the home 🌿

Photos by @benhoskingphotographer
Words by @nat_twiss for @type7

node.text:
The culture on the French Riviera is unique. Between the Cannes film festival, the Monaco Grand Prix, and the grand hotels of Saint-Tropez, sometimes we even forget that this region of the world belongs to the real world.

For those of us who grew up here, it's part of our fabric. The Italians have the dolce vita, and likewise on the French Riviera there is a form of relaxed and inimitable elegance, even when we’re taking a 996 Carrera 4 convertible up the hills so we can skate our way down.

Words by @ggggound
Photos by @amen.three
